==English==

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌpə(r)|-ʌpə(r)]]

===Noun===
'''upper''' (''plural:'' '''uppers''')

# The piece of [[leather]] etc. that forms the part of a [[shoe]] above the [[sole]].
# A [[stimulant]] such as [[Amphetamine]] that increases [[energy]] and decreases [[appetite]].

===Adjective===
'''upper'''

# At a [[higher]] [[level]], [[rank]] or [[position]]
# [[Situate]]d on higher ground, further inland, or more northerly.
# (Archaeology and Geology) of a later [[division]] of some [[period]]
# (Politics) In a [[bicameral]] system, the generally smaller and less representative house.

